Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Expansion of Metric in FN Coordinates", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.926483787574461*^9, 
  3.926483840777058*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"fb6dda7d-7497-f44b-b9d3-\
09900181d85c"],

Cell["\<\
The Fermi Normal Coordinates, is adapted to a timelike geodesic (we can show \
that it actually works for an arbitrary curve by Fermi-Walker transport of \
tetrads which generalizes the parallel transport along a geodesic in this \
case). To First order the metric in this coordinates resembles the Minkowski \
(Flat space time metric), and hence the derivative of the metric vanishes and \
consequently the Christoffel Symbols. It is also possible to show that we \
cannot make any further derivatives of the metric vanish simultaneously using \
the independent degree of freedom available from the symmetries. And we \
conclude that it represents the intrinsic curvature of the spacetime, and \
those higher order terms are related to the Riemann Curvature tensor and its \
derivatives as we shall derive in the following sections.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9265632967280483`*^9, 
  3.926563585593914*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"8581b2d6-f3e7-5144-b110-\
0f5a0e57c392"],

