Cell["\<\
The relation between Riemann Curvature tensor and the Christoffel Symbols\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.926391134336061*^9, 3.926391153999229*^9}, {
  3.926391191246926*^9, 3.926391191547011*^9}, {3.926391302622809*^9, 
  3.926391348385231*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c06eb07d-f9ad-c84a-b73c-\
4c6ae36416cc"]
}, Closed]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
Relations among the Riemann and Christoffel from G.Deviation equation\
\>", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9264887674250736`*^9, 
  3.92648879025725*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a8c00bc6-d752-2d45-ae19-\
74f91c37585e"],

Cell["\<\
We will derive the equations/identities we now define as rules in a section. \
We know it is easier to connect the derivatives of the metric tensor in terms \
of Christoffel symbols and its derivatives, following by the \
relations/identities relating the Derivatives of Christoffel symbols to the \
Riemann Curvature tensor. This is the logic we will be following throughout \
the notebook. As mentioned above, we will make these relations as rules now \
without their derivation, and will try to derive those in another sections.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9264912889698734`*^9, 3.926491362975317*^9}, {
  3.926493090943308*^9, 3.9264931134279213`*^9}, {3.926564400597658*^9, 
  3.9265646075945015`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a965cfbc-30d9-9744-ae06-\
dc927d80ad6e"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"rule23", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"PDPDChristoffelCD", "[", 
